title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland Auditorium Arena on 1979-12-28
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/96k) -> Samplitude Professional v9.12 -> Adobe Audition v1.5 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Sugaree, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Row Jimmy, It's All Over Now, High Time, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Uncle John's Band-> I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Good Lovin', E: Casey Jones, E: One More Saturday Night*

*Second Encore

reviews.review_text: Complete opposite opposite to the review below only because we all like some shows others might not like. That being said this the hottest intro to Music Never stopped . Crystal clear sound here also might have some hiss but after all these years most old recordings dew.

Really like this show Never gave it much of a listen before but didn't really like the choices for todays "This day in GD history" so jumped to this one.

Like the sound a lot.  High energy GSET and the AUD has a nice feel to it.
